# Porting Standard: PrintFlowLite ‚Üí PrintFlow

When porting features from PrintFlowLite Java code to PrintFlow TypeScript, follow these rules:

## 1. Read the Source First

Before implementing any feature, find the corresponding PrintFlowLite source:
- Auth/Sessions ‚Üí `SpSession.java`, `UserService.java`, `RestAuthFilter.java`
- User Management ‚Üí `UserService.java`, `UserGroupService.java`, `UserCardService.java`
- SafePages ‚Üí `DocIn.java`, `DocStoreService.java`, `InboxService.java`
- Print Release ‚Üí `ProxyPrintService.java`, `PrintOutService.java`
- IPP Printing ‚Üí `IppPrintServer.java`
- Page Editor ‚Üí `jquery.printflowlite-canvas-editor.js`
- Financial ‚Üí `AccountingService.java`, `AccountService.java`, `AccountVoucherService.java`
- Job Tickets ‚Üí `JobTicketService.java`, `WebAppJobTickets.java`
- Reports ‚Üí `RestReportsService.java`
- Email ‚Üí `EmailService.java`
- PDF ‚Üí `PdfOutService.java`
- LibreOffice ‚Üí `SOfficeService.java`
- PGP ‚Üí `lib/pgp/pdf/PGPHelper.java`

## 2. Preserve Logic, Not Syntax

- Port the **business logic**, not the Java syntax
- Use TypeScript idioms: `async/await`, `Map`, `Set`, arrow functions
- Use Drizzle ORM instead of JPA ‚Äî map entities to schema tables 1:1
- Use Zod for validation instead of Java bean validation

## 3. Database Schema Naming

Table names in PrintFlow Drizzle schema **MUST match PrintFlowLite**:
- `tbl_user` ‚Üê `User.java`
- `tbl_session` ‚Üê `SpSession.java`
- `tbl_user_account` ‚Üê `UserAccount.java`
- `tbl_printer` ‚Üê `Printer.java`
- `tbl_doc_in` ‚Üê `DocIn.java`
- `tbl_doc_log` ‚Üê `DocLog.java`

## 4. Error Handling

Port error codes from PrintFlowLite:
- `INVALID_CREDENTIALS`, `ACCOUNT_INACTIVE`, `TOTP_REQUIRED`, `TOTP_INVALID`
- `USERNAME_EXISTS`, `USER_NOT_FOUND`, `INVALID_PASSWORD`

## 5. Comment the Source

Add a comment at the top of every ported file:
```typescript
// Ported from PrintFlowLite: <OriginalFile.java>
// Original logic: <brief description>
```

## 6. What NOT to Port

Skip these from PrintFlowLite:
- Apache Wicket UI components (replace with Next.js)
- Java Servlet filters (replace with Fastify middleware)
- CometD WebSocket (replace with tRPC + SSE)
- Java-specific crypto (replace with Node.js `crypto`)
- JasperReports (replace with Recharts)
- BouncyCastle PGP (replace with `openpgp` library)
- YubiKey TOTP (replace with `otplib`)
- Java IPP (replace with `node-ipp`)

## 7. Keep Working Tests

Every ported feature **MUST have tests** before considering complete:
- Unit tests for business logic
- API tests for endpoints
- Tests run via `pnpm test` in the monorepo root
